Troubleshooting Tips
VECTR won't start:

Check Docker service: sudo systemctl status docker
View logs: docker-compose logs -f
Ensure ports 8081 and 27017 are available
API authentication fails:

Verify credentials are correct
Check token is included in request headers
Ensure HTTPS is used (not HTTP)
Activities not logging:

Verify campaign ID is correct
Check technique exists in campaign before logging activity
Ensure JSON payload matches API schema
Report generation errors:

Confirm campaign has activities to report
Check file write permissions in output directory
Validate JSON structure before writing
Conclusion
This lab demonstrated how to integrate VECTR into Red Team operations for systematic documentation and reporting. You learned to deploy VECTR, interact with its API using Python, document MITRE ATT&CK techniques, log activities in real-time, and generate comprehensive reports. These skills are essential for professional Red Team operations, enabling better communication with stakeholders, tracking campaign progress, and maintaining detailed records for post-engagement analysis. The automation techniques you developed can be extended to integrate VECTR with other Red Team tools and workflows, creating a comprehensive operation tracking system.
